-- Hareon Solar Plans $1.6 Billion of Solar Farms in Inner Mongolia
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-11-21T08:01:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-21/hareon-solar-plans-1-6-billion-of-solar-farms-in-inner-mongolia.html
Hareon Solar Technology Co. (600401) , a
Chinese maker of solar panels, plans to invest 10 billion  yuan 
($1.6 billion) in 1 gigawatt of solar power projects in Chinaâ€™s
northern province of Inner Mongolia.  The developments will be in the Alashan region 1,200
kilometers (746 miles) west of Beijing where the local
government has signed a letter of intent, Hareon said yesterday
in a statement to the Shanghai stock exchange.  Construction of the first 100 megawatts, costing 1 billion
yuan, is expected to be completed next year, the Jiangyin,
Jiangsu-based company said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
